The paper deals with computational complexity and approximability of cut problems in directed graphs, which are fundamental topics in computer science. The techniques used in the paper are combinatorial, based on LPs and enumeration of approximate min-cuts, which are commonly used in algorithms and discrete mathematics. The paper also presents NP-completeness and inapproximability results, which are typical topics in computational complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
